The paper deals with the application of machine learning models for the estimation of magnet temperature in permanent magnet synchronous motors. This involves the use of supervised learning algorithms to predict high-dynamic magnet temperature profiles. The paper discusses the empirical evaluation of several machine learning models, including ordinary and weighted least squares, support vector regression, k-nearest neighbors, randomized trees, and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
